The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning techniques to construct strategies for agents in social dilemmas, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses game theory and the use of strategies, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of deep reinforcement learning techniques also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper discusses multi-agent interaction, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the need for understanding both the consequences of and the intentions behind an action, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
